# JavaScript Formatter

This rule defines formatting guidelines for JavaScript and related files.

<rule>
name: js_formatter
description: JavaScript code formatting standards for this project

filters:
  - type: file_extension
    pattern: "\\.(js|jsx|ts|tsx|svelte)$"
  - type: event
    pattern: "file_edit"

actions:
  - type: suggest
    message: |
      JavaScript code must follow these formatting rules:

      1. Use 2 spaces for indentation (no tabs)
      2. Maximum line length is 100 characters
      3. Use single quotes for strings
      4. Include trailing commas where valid in ES5
      5. Use semicolons at the end of statements
      6. No trailing whitespace
      7. End files with a single newline

      Example of properly formatted code:
      ```javascript
      function calculateTotal(items) {
        const total = items
          .map((item) => item.price * item.quantity)
          .reduce((sum, value) => sum + value, 0);
        
        return total;
      }
      
      const config = {
        apiUrl: 'https://api.example.com',
        timeout: 3000,
        retries: 3,
      };
      ```

examples:
  - input: |
      function badlyFormattedFunction(param1,param2,param3 = "default"){
      var x=param1+param2;return(x)}
  - output: |
      function badlyFormattedFunction(param1, param2, param3 = 'default') {
        const x = param1 + param2;
        return x;
      }

metadata:
  priority: medium
  version: 1.0
</rule>

